and 21st century not as something solid, but as a malleable figure in a play which is constantly being restaged. Caspar Battegay's essay looks into this play of figures of Jewishness in a selection of extremely diverse films, TV series, songs and texts. In the process, not only is a new research area in Jewish Studies in Germany created - the theory of pop culture is also enriched through the previously neglected Jewish dimension.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAmerikanische Kultur. 4aDeutsch-jüdische Kulturgeschichte. 4aIdentität. 4aJudentum. 4aJüdische Geschichte. 4aJüdische Studien. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLeonard Cohen. 4aMedienästhetik. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aJewish Studies.  aJudaism.  aMedia Aesthetics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Lit. & Kultur 2010-2013z978311037074440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839420478zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839420478423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839420478/original  a978-3-11-037074-4  transcript Highlight Collection Lit. & Kultur 2010-2013c2010d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TSOc2010d2013